### Target Users / Personas

**Primary Persona: Ramesh Kumar - Small Farmer**

- **Demographics:**
  - Age: 35-50 years
  - Location: Rural Punjab (Ludhiana district)
  - Occupation: Small farmer (2-3 acres)
  - Tech Savviness: Low (basic smartphone usage)
  - Languages: Punjabi (primary), limited Hindi
  - Education: Primary to 10th standard

- **Goals & Motivations:**
  - Increase crop yield to support family
  - Reduce fertilizer and pesticide costs
  - Learn modern farming techniques
  - Get timely weather information
  - Identify crop diseases early

- **Pain Points:**
  - Cannot read English agricultural content
  - Poor internet connectivity in village
  - Relies on shopkeeper advice (often biased)
  - Loses crops to unexpected weather/pests
  - Struggles with smartphone apps (too complex)

- **User Needs:**
  - Voice-based guidance in Punjabi
  - Simple, icon-based navigation
  - Works without internet
  - Quick answers to farming questions
  - Trustworthy, government-backed information

**Secondary Persona: Lakshmi Devi - Marginal Farmer**

- **Demographics:**
  - Age: 28-45 years
  - Location: Rural Tamil Nadu
  - Occupation: Marginal farmer (0.5-1 acre)
  - Tech Savviness: Low (borrowed smartphone)
  - Languages: Tamil (primary)
  - Education: Limited formal education

- **Goals & Motivations:**
  - Maximize income from small land
  - Learn about government schemes
  - Get advice on vegetable farming
  - Avoid crop losses

- **Pain Points:**
  - Limited smartphone ownership
  - Very low digital literacy
  - Language barrier with most apps
  - Cannot afford expensive inputs

- **User Needs:**
  - Extremely simple interface
  - Audio-first experience
  - Free access to information
  - Support for feature phones (future)

**Tertiary Persona: Anil Sharma - Agricultural Extension Officer**

- **Demographics:**
  - Age: 30-45 years
  - Location: District agriculture office
  - Occupation: Government agricultural officer
  - Tech Savviness: Medium-High
  - Languages: Hindi, Punjabi, English

- **Goals & Motivations:**
  - Reach more farmers efficiently
  - Track advisory impact
  - Share localized farming knowledge
  - Improve department metrics

- **Pain Points:**
  - Cannot physically visit all farmers
  - Lack of data on farmer needs
  - Limited tools for mass communication

- **User Needs:**
  - Dashboard to monitor app usage
  - Ability to push advisories to farmers
  - Analytics on farmer engagement
  - Easy content management

