### Typography

**Google Fonts for React Native:**

**Font Integration:**
```bash
# Install fonts
npx react-native-asset
```

**fonts.json:**
```json
{
  "project": {
    "android": {
      "assets": ["./assets/fonts"]
    }
  }
}
```

**Font Files Required:**
- Noto Sans (Latin + Devanagari + Tamil + Telugu)
- Noto Sans Punjabi (Gurmukhi script)
- Font weights: 400, 500, 600, 700

**Font System:**

**Primary Font (UI & Body):**
- **Font Family:** Noto Sans
- **Weights:** 400 (Regular), 500 (Medium), 600 (SemiBold), 700 (Bold)
- **Usage:** All UI elements, body text, buttons, labels
- **Characteristics:** Highly readable, extensive Unicode support, optimized for Indian languages
- **Why:** Noto Sans supports Devanagari, Gurmukhi, Tamil, Telugu with consistent styling

**Typography Scale (Mobile-Optimized):**

```tsx
/* Heading Styles */
H1 (Screen Title): 28px / 36px - font-weight: 700 - Used for: Main screen headings
H2 (Section): 24px / 32px - font-weight: 600 - Used for: Section titles
H3 (Card Title): 20px / 28px - font-weight: 600 - Used for: Card headings
H4 (Subtitle): 18px / 26px - font-weight: 500 - Used for: Subtitles

/* Body Styles */
Body Large: 18px / 26px - font-weight: 400 - Used for: Primary instructions
Body Regular: 16px / 24px - font-weight: 400 - Used for: Standard text
Body Small: 14px / 20px - font-weight: 400 - Used for: Supporting text

/* UI Elements */
Button Text: 16px / 24px - font-weight: 600 - Used for: Button labels
Label: 14px / 20px - font-weight: 500 - Used for: Form labels
Caption: 12px / 16px - font-weight: 400 - Used for: Timestamps, metadata
```

**Multilingual Typography Considerations:**

- **Devanagari (Hindi):** Slightly larger line-height (1.6x) for diacritics
- **Gurmukhi (Punjabi):** Adequate spacing for top-heavy glyphs
- **Tamil/Telugu:** Extended character set support
- **All Scripts:** Minimum 16px for body text (outdoor readability)

**Responsive Typography:**

- **Small Phones (<360px):** -2px from base sizes
- **Standard (360px-400px):** Base sizes as defined
- **Large Phones (>400px):** +2px for headings only

